It's great for beginners intro to health food but the quality is NOT there..at least for me and my family. Nice marketing though. Unfortunately not organic and the staff at the front desk didn't have much knowledge on the ingredients or quality. Things like the protein powder just come "prepackaged in big boxes." Alot of "healthy" juice bars are everywhere now but I do hope they step up their quality with all the gmo and Round up in the produce nowadays. I really dont even want to talk about the plastic. I wish the best for this space and all juice bars like these.

So today, a friend wanted to show me a new juice bar he found in Aventura. We went, expecting the same experience that I've had at any other juice bar. While my friend wanted a protein bowl he legit said " is there really protein in here, it's so good" as I am writing this. So good I even tried it and was like wow the peanut butter topped on it absolutely made the whole bowl for me. Surprisingly, I am actually incredibly impressed with the bowls. Generally speaking the flavors are usually generic, but Nekter really finds a way to make this a unique experience, and many different flavors and textures hitting your tastebuds. Furthermore this Orange Crush is the exact kind of juice I like. Icey, fruity, but not where the acidity of the juice is overpowering. An incredible balance for a hot day after a long run.  Had to try the Vegen Frozen treats, first the chocolate, and after making a comment about how I am not a fan of coconut, Margo says she is not either, but loves the Coconut Vanilla, thus of course how could I Resist trying it myself now. WOW, I am now a fan of coconut vanilla as well. Absolutely will be the next thing I have when I come back tomorrow after working out, with another Orange Crush.  My friend will likely be getting another protein powerbowl, possibly I will be stealing his next time too.
